==Storylines==
====MAD Lions Return to Play-Ins====
In their third consecutive Worlds appearance, [[MAD Lions]] once again find themselves in the Play-In stage, which previously knocked them out in 19-20th place to make them the first major region team in history to fail making it to the group stage. With more major region representatives in the event than ever before, one major region team is guaranteed to be eliminated in Play-Ins, which [[MAD Lions]] will hope to avoid this time around.

====T1's Last Minute Coaching Changes====
Following a drop in form in the [[LCK/2022/Summer|LCK 2022 Summer Split]], [[T1]] announced coaching staff changes with [[Bengi]] moving to the head coach position and [[Sky_(Kim_Ha-neul)|Sky]] joining from [[T1 Academy]] as a new coaching staff member.

====Kaori in for Evil Geniuses====
Following the choice by [[Danny]] to take a step back from the starting roster<ref name="Danny inactive">{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/totheLaPointe/status/1567180951842689029 |title=With love regarding our League roster for Chicago. |date=2022-09-06 |author=[[totheLapointe]] |publisher=Twitter |language={{flag/usuk}} English}}</ref>, [[Kaori]] moved up from [[Evil Geniuses Academy]]<ref name="Kaori promoted">{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/EvilGeniuses/status/1567588520323055618 |title=Big stage, big call up. |date=2022-09-07 |author=[[Evil Geniuses]] |publisher=Twitter |language={{flag/usuk}} English}}</ref>, taking [[100 Thieves]] to 5 games in the [[LCS/2022/Summer/Playoffs|LCS 2022 Summer Playoffs]]. With just a single LCS match under their belt and no international experience, [[Kaori]] will be looking to fill Danny's shoes for the team.

